You need to increase the `http.max_content_length` in your `elasticsearch.yml` config file. 

By default, it is set at 100MB (100*1024*1024 = 104857600), so you probably need to set it a little higher than that.

**UPDATE**

It is actually a different issue, which is explained [here](https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/client/java-rest/current/java-rest-low-usage-requests.html). Basically, the default `HttpAsyncResponseConsumerFactory` buffers the whole response body in the heap memory, but only up to 100mb by default. The workaround is to configure another size for that buffer, but your only option is to work with the low-level REST client instead. In ES 7, you&#39;ll be able to do this on the High-level REST client using a class called `RequestOptions`, but it&#39;s not released yet.

